<subSubSection pageId="36" pageNumber="37" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="36.[151,1437,258,393]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,290,258,284]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">Comments:</emphasis>
As the two previous morphospecies, the identification of the single collected individual to the species level was not possible because the individual is a female. The fastigium of the frons presents a white ocellus. The fastigium of the vertex is rhomboid, and light-yellow, longer than large. The tegmina bear a black stain on the beginning of A2 vein. The ovipositor is a little shorter than the length of the abdomen.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
